BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:ONG5FB9nHhwPx_6nva6_q
SUMMARY:Boren Banner Series: Camille Trautman
DTSTAMP:20260316T010605Z
DTSTART:20260325T180000Z
DESCRIPTION:Every photograph is a reminder that the act of framing is never
	 neutral. In Camille Trautman’s first solo museum exhibition in their home
	town\, the Seattle-born Duwamish artist uses photography and video to chal
	lenge colonial narratives and counter Indigenous erasure. The exhibition p
	resents selections from their ongoing series The North American LCD—spectr
	al self-portraits staged in varied natural landscapes. Rooted in Trautman’
	s process of coming out as transgender\, the images show the artist’s body
	 partially obscured by large LCD screens. The series examines how both lan
	dscape photography and digital media can shape or distort cultural identit
	y\, often by promoting or denying visibility.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.
	com/events/#/details/boren-banner-series-camille-trautman/16813305/2026-03
	-25T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Community & Civic
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/boren-banner-series-camil
	le-trautman/16813305/2026-03-25T00
LOCATION:Frye Art Museum\, 704 Terry Ave\, Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-community
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Community & Civic
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT6H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:gBC3ZVsCWPlxz8nq4yhD0
SUMMARY:Squak Mountain Celebration Hike
DTSTAMP:20260316T010605Z
DTSTART:20260325T190000Z
DESCRIPTION:Join IATC Vice President Selena Eon for an afternoon hike on Sq
	uak Mountain to celebrate all of the hard work volunteer crews have put in
	 to restore these trails in the wake of the 2024 bomb cyclone. Throughout 
	2025\, over 130 IATC volunteers worked to remove debris and restore tread 
	to trails on Squak over the course of 25 work parties.  We’ll meet at Moun
	tainside Drive Trailhead \\(also known as Bullitt Fireplace Trailhead\\) a
	nd work our way up to Old Griz\, where a substantial portion of the 2025 t
	rail work took place. We’ll also view the landslide sites on Phil’s Creek 
	before heading down the Eastside Trail back to the trailhead. Trails: Moun
	tainside Drive Trail\, Old Griz\, Phil’s Creek\, Eastside Trail Meeting Lo
	cation: Mountainside Drive Trailhead Date & Time: Wednesday\, March 25th\,
	 12:00 PM - 5:00 PM Duration: 5 hours Distance: 5 miles Elevation Gain: 13
	00 feet NOTE: This hike includes 1300 feet of elevation gain over 5 miles\
	, making it a moderate to difficult hike.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/
	events/#/details/squak-mountain-celebration-hike/18270843/2026-03-25T00\n\
	nFrom SEAtoday - All Events
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/squak-mountain-celebratio
	n-hike/18270843/2026-03-25T00
LOCATION:Squak Mtn- Bullitt Fireplace Trailhead\, Mountainside Dr SW\, Issa
	quah\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-all
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - All Events
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT5H
END:VEVENT
